Resources for Flexbox ideas:
https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/CSS_Flexible_Box_Layout/Typical_Use_Cases_of_Flexbox
https://www.joshwcomeau.com/css/interactive-guide-to-flexbox/

- New way to arrange items into rows or columns

flex container:
- elemenet has the display: flex on it

flex container properties:
- flex-direction: Defines in which direction the container wants to stack the flex items
  - column: stacks them vertically
  - column-reverse: stacs them vertically but from bottom to top
  - row: stacks the items horizontall
  - row-reverse: stacks items horizontally but from right to left

- flex-wrap: Specifies whether the flex items should wrap or not
  - nowrap: Flex items will not wrap (this is default)
  - wrap-reverse: items will wrap but in reverse order

- flex-flow: shorthand for setting both the flex-direction and flex-wrap properties
  - row wrap: sets the direction to row and wrap to wrap

- justify-content: Used to align the flex items
  - center: aligns the flex items at the center of the container
  - flex-start: aligns the flex items at the beginning of the container (this is default)
  - flex-end: aligns the items at the end of the container
  - space-around: displays the flex items with space before, between, and after the lines
  - space-between: displays the flex items with the space between the lines

- align-items: Used to alignn the flex items
  - center: aligns items in the center of the container
  - flex-start: aligns the flex items at the top of the container
  - flex-end: aligns the flex items at the bottom of the container
  - stretch: stretches the flex items to fill the container (this is default)
  - baselien: aligns the flex items such as their baseline aligns

- align-content: Aligns the flex lines
  - space-between: displays the flex lines with equal space between them
  - space-around: displays the flex lines with space before, between, and after them
  - stretch: stretches the flex lines to take up the remaining space (this is default)
  - center: displays the flex lines in the middle of the container
  - flex-start: displays the flex lines at the start of the container
  - flex-end: displays the flex lines at the end of the container

flex shorthand:
- flex declaration is a shorthand for;
  flex-grow
  flex-shrink
  flex-basis


Flex item properties:
- order: specifies the order of the flex items
  - order value must be a number. Default is 0.

- flex-grow: specifies how much a flex item will grow relative to the rest of the flex items
  - value must be a number. Default is 0.

- flex-shrink: specifies how much a flex item will shrink relative to the rest of the flex items
  - value must be a number. Default is 1.

- flex-basis: specifies the initial length of flex item
  - example flex-basis: 200px

- flex: shorthand for flex-grow, flex-shrink, and flex-basis

- align-self: specifies the alignment for the selected item inside the flexible container
  - Overrides container's align-items property
  - example align-self: center/flex-start/flex-end etc.

